      • getOptimizeRadius

        public static int getOptimizeRadius()
        After a path is generated, it is cleaned up by removing tiles that are very close to each other. This setting determines how close this should be. Change this if you have issues with running around walls. Default value is 5. Gets how close a tile should be to another one to remove it from the path.
        Returns:
        distance in number of tiles.

      • setOptimizeRadius

        public static void setOptimizeRadius(int value)
        After a path is generated, it is cleaned up by removing tiles that are very close to each other. This setting determines how close this should be. Change this if you have issues with running around walls. Default value is 5. Sets how close a tile should be to another one to remove it from the path.
        Parameters:
        value -
